Bishop Bheki Ngcobo of the South African Zionist Church is defying the ban on mass gatherings. He vows his congregants will worship the Lord this Easter. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Bishop Bheki Ngcobo of the South African Zionist Church is defying the ban on mass gatherings. He vows his congregants will worship the Lord this Easter. READ: No COVID-19 vaccine yet: Health minister "If this thing is so serious why you don't stop the companies to operate. You give the companies the option of applying precautions and you don't give us those precaution measures." "If we stop God from operating do you think we can survive in the economy as well? I chose God without consulting the government." Coronavirus: ZCC cancels all Moria events until further notice President Cyril Ramaphosa announced measures Cabinet decided to implement to reduce the impact of the virus. One of those measures includes the prohibition of gatherings of more than 100 people. The number of people infected by the coronavirus in South Africa has soared to 202. There are 52 new infections with Gauteng still being the epicentre of the virus. Over 60 percent of South Africans will feel the direct impact of COVID-19, even if they don't contract the virus. More local transmissions are being recorded.  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.